overview: The user wanted to enhance their sleep questionnaire application by
  adding a database to store responses, an admin dashboard for data access, and
  an authentication system. The plan involved updating the demographics data
  structure, creating a  model in Prisma for a PostgreSQL
  database (NeonDB), and implementing API routes for saving, retrieving, and
  exporting questionnaire data as CSV. A key decision was to build a simple
  admin dashboard with password-based authentication. Initially, a custom
  session management system was implemented, but it was later simplified by
  leveraging Next.js middleware for route protection and a basic cookie-based
  authentication. The implementation covered all aspects, from schema updates
  and API development to UI for the admin dashboard. Extensive testing confirmed
  that the database saving, data retrieval, CSV export, admin login, logout, and
  middleware protection were all fully functional.
